In [2]:
def make_dir_df(set_dir):
    classes = os.listdir(set_dir)
    df=pd.DataFrame(columns=['class','dir'])
    for c in classes:
        full_dir = os.path.join(set_dir,c)
        df= df.append(
        pd.DataFrame({'class': c,
                      'dir':os.listdir(full_dir)})
        )
    df.reset_index(drop=True,inplace=True)
    df['dir']= set_dir+df['class']+'/' +df['dir']
    return df

data_train = make_dir_df('train/')
data_test = make_dir_df('test/')
data_train.head()

In [8]:
def getshape(df):
    shapedf = df.loc[:,'dir'].apply(lambda x :cv2.imread(x).shape[:-1])
    df['rows'] =  shapedf.apply(lambda x :x[0]).astype(int)
    df['cols'] = shapedf.apply(lambda x :x[1]).astype(int)
    return df

data_train = getshape(data_train)
data_test = getshape(data_test)

In [39]:
nrows = 2
ncols = 5

def show_image_sample(pic_directory):
    '''display 5x5 images'''
    fig = plt.gcf()
    fig.set_size_inches(ncols * 5, nrows * 5)
    for i, img_path in enumerate(image_list):
        sp = plt.subplot(nrows, ncols, i + 1)
        img = cv2.cvtColor(cv2.imread(img_path),  cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        img = cv2.resize(img, (160,160), interpolation = cv2.INTER_AREA)
        sp.axis('Off')
        plt.imshow(img)
    plt.show()
    
show_image_sample(image_list)
